import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distance?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["distance"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance between points?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
